<TITLE> Children, who fell ill eating WFP food, leave hospital </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Khagrhachharhi, June 2 (bdnews24.com)The students who had fallen sick on Monday after eating biscuits distributed by the WFP in the hilly Khagrhachharhi district were discharged from local hospitals on Tuesday after treatment. The local civil surgeon, Dr Abu Taher, said the students were all right. The biscuits in question have been sent to Dhaka for laboratory tests into their toxicity and other properties, he confirmed At least 428 primary school students were suffering from food poisoning in two remote upazilas of the district, Laxmichhari and Mohalchhari. Most were admitted to upazila health complexes at Laxmichhari, Manikchhari and Mohalchhari. Some were taken to Chittagong Medical College Hospital. Dr Taher told bdnews24.com on Monday that the children had been suffering from stomach ache and diarrhoea. Laxmichhai upazila chairman Ramrachay Chowdhury said children of Monghapara, Jaindrapara, Debolchhari and Jharolchhari were the worst affected in number. District civil surgeon and deputy commissioner Md Khalilur Rahman and local officials visited the areas. WFP distributes food among primary school children, in partnership with local NGO Kabidang, under a schools feeding programme. bd
